FormControl.Name: txtProfileName
FormControl.ToolTip: The name of the profile

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerIntervalInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies how often the system should check for the in-memory worker tasks that are pending.

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerDBIntervalInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies how often the system should poll for a due database worker tasks.

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerResetTaskIntervalInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies how often the system checks for the timed-out worker tasks.

FormControl.Name: txtMaximumNumberOfEvaluateJobTasksToTake
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the maximum number of Evaluate Job tasks to take.

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerThreadPoolMonitoringIntervalInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting defines how often automatic activity thread pools are monitored for timeout.

FormControl.Name: txtArchiveDeleteWorkerTasksToRetrieve
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the number of Archive Jobs and DeleteItem non-system level worker tasks to retrieve for execution.

Label.Name: label1
Label.Text: Archive delete worker tasks to retrieve

FormControl.Name: txtArchiveDeleteRetryIntervalInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the maximum duration in seconds to calculate the next due date for executing Archive Jobs and DeleteItem non-system level worker tasks.

FormControl.Name: txtUpgradeJobsThreadPoolSize
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the size of the upgrade job thread pool. If the thread pool size is full, the Core Worker waits until there is space to add more tasks.

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerActivityTimeoutIntervalInMinutes
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting defines the duration after which an activity is timed out. The activity is only available once the corresponding task executes.

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerResetActivityIntervalInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies how often the system should poll for the due database worker tasks.

FormControl.Name: txtImportConnectorName
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting allows administrators to explicitly specify the import connection a Core Worker should use. (Default: All) This setting is useful when multiple Core Workers are set up.

FormControl.Name: txtMaximumNumberOfMessagesToImport
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the maximum number of documents or messages to import for document ingest.

FormControl.Name: txtCoreWorkerWorkQueueSize
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the maximum number of tasks that can be taken by the Core Worker.

FormControl.Name: txtMaximumNumberOfActivitiesToLock
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the number of automatic activities to lock when the Core Worker polls for execution of automatic activities.

Label.Name: label1
Label.Text: Maximum number of activities to lock

FormControl.Name: ddActivityOrder
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the order in which the activities are taken for processing

FormControl.Name: txtAutoActivitiesPoolName
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the thread pool name for automatic activities.

FormControl.Name: txtAutoActivitiesPoolId
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the thread pool ID for automatic activities.

FormControl.Name: txtMaximumDirectIngestThreads
FormControl.ToolTip: Maximum number of direct import threads per tenant

FormControl.Name: txtDirectIngestBurstDurationInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: This setting specifies the maximum duration since the start of a worker thread where it continuously imports the available messages. It usually terminates the earlier if no input is due for polling. If this duration is reached, then the worker thread completes after the current import/poll operation.

FormControl.Name: txtDirectIngestTimeoutInSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: Maximum run duration (2h) of direct import worker threads. The worker threads are cancelled if this time-out expires. It must be higher than the expected worst-case duration for reception and import of a message

FormControl.Name: txtDirectIngestConfirmTimeoutSeconds
FormControl.ToolTip: Maximum confirm retry duration

Confirmation.Message: Are you sure you want to delete this profile? If any agent is using this profile, when the refresh interval passes, the settings will be reverted to default settings.
